---
layout: recipe
title: Cranberry, Apple, and Ginger Chutney
from: All Recipes Magazine
fromurl: 
time: 20 minutes
---

Ingredients:
------------

* 4 cups cranberries
* 1/2 cup sugars
* 3/4 cups brown sugar
* 2 tsp cinnamon
* 1 tsp minced ginger
* 1/4 tsp ground cloves
* 1 cup water
* 1/2 cup finely chopped celery
* 1/2 cup chopped apple

<br>

Directions:
-----------

1. Combine cranberries, both sugars, spices and water in a saucepan
2. Bring to boil then simmer over low heat until berries start to pop.
3. Add apple and celery and continue to cook, stirring occassionally, until thick
4. Transfer to mason jars and store, refrigerated, for up to a year.
